description: Harvey Dent, now calling himself Two-Face, resurfaces and starts robbing Rupert Thorne's illegal businesses, preparing for a final confrontation with the crime boss, and Batman must stop his former friend before he and Thorne kill each other.
name: Two-Face, Part Two

description: Darkwing is blinded by Megavolt
name: Duck Blind

description: CAN OLIVER OUTWIT OR OUTFIGHT THE DARK ARCHER TO SAVE THE CITY? — With the Undertaking days away, Malcolm (guest star John Barrowman) dons his black hood to conclude business with seismologist Dr. Brion Markov (guest star Eric Floyd) and his team. Oliver and Moira entertain a number of surprise – and mostly unwelcome – visitors. Hooded confrontations at home and the Meryln Global Group reveal dark secrets. Meanwhile, Roy (guest star Colton Haynes) and Thea are still looking out for a hero. Laurel makes a decision after Tommy’s revelation. In a flashback to the island, Oliver, Slade (guest star Manu Bennett) and Shado (guest star Celina Jade) struggle to prevent Fyers (guest star Sebastian Dunn) from shooting a Ferris Air jet out of the sky. Paul Blackthorne and David Ramsey also star. Roger Cross and Bryon Mann also guest star. John Behring directed the episode written by Drew Z. Greenberg & Wendy Mericle.
name: Darkness on the Edge of Town

deck: After finding a rather telling photograph, Mulder questions his father's involvement in a government conspiracy.
name: Paper Clip

description: A mob war between crime bosses Rupert Thorne and Arnold Stromwell is nearing its end, and comes to a climax when Stromwell is set up to be killed in an exploding restaurant by Thorne. Batman saves him at the last moment, and aided by Stromwell's brother (now a priest who lost his leg years before, an accident for which Stromwell carries a secret guilt), tries to persuade him to give up his life of crime and help the police bring Thorne down by testifying against him.
name: It's Never Too Late

deck: A young man is struck by lightning, and appears to gain unusual powers.
name: D.P.O.

description: Showing Off His Techniques! Zoro's Formidable One-Sword Style! (奥義炸裂! ゾロ最強の一刀流!, Ōgi Sakuretsu! Zoro Saikyō no Ittō-ryū!)
name: Showing Off His Techniques! Zoro's Formidable One-Sword Style!

description: A pair of teenage junior detectives accompanied with their teen rivals set to protect Batman from the violent revenge of the criminal Penguin.
name: I've Got Batman In My Basement

description:
Darkwing tries to write a comic book

trivia: inspiration for Deathvalley Duck (aka the cowboy alterante reality version of Darkwing Duck) of the Darkwings of the Multiverse was taken from this episode.
name: Comic Book Capers

description: HEROES ARE FORGED AND SACRIFICES MADE IN THIS EPIC SEASON FINALE — Oliver and Diggle race to stop the Dark Archer from unleashing his vengeance on The Glades. However, they run into a roadblock after Detective Lance picks up Felicity for questioning. Tommy and Oliver’s already tumultuous relationship takes a turn for the worse after Oliver makes a confession about Laurel. After hearing of the danger in The Glades, Thea races to find Roy, inadvertently putting herself directly in the line of fire for Malcolm’s devious plan. On the island, Oliver, Slade and Shado (guest star Celina Jade) are locked in a life-or-death struggle against Fyers (guest star Sebastian Dunn) as his missiles lock on a full Ferris Air jetliner. Susanna Thompson also stars. David Barrett directed the episode with the teleplay written by Marc Guggenheim & Andrew Kreisberg and story by Greg Berlanti.
name: Sacrifice

deck: Mulder and Scully enlist the help of a reluctant psychic who appears to have a mental connection to a psychotic killer.
name: Clyde Bruckman's Final Repose

deck: After a man is executed, the people he swore revenge on begin to die in unexplained ways.
name: The List

deck: A creature uses online dating to prey on overweight, insecure women.
name: 2Shy

deck: An investigation at a veteran's hospital takes a strange turn when all evidence points to the most unlikely suspect.
name: The Walk

description:
Japanese title: Sanjō! Uzumaki Naruto!" (参上!うずまきナルト)

Welcome to the Village Hidden in the Leaves, where deadly serious ninja roam the land and the seriously mischievous Naruto Uzumaki causes trouble everywhere he goes.
name: He Appears! Naruto Uzumaki

deck: Mulder and Scully investigate a kidnapping case.
description:
Plot Summary

A teenage girl is lucky to escape after being kidnapped and kept in a locked room. But when she collapses years later at the exact moment another girl is snatched, the evidence soon suggests that she has a inexplicable bond with her abductor's latest victim.
name: Oubliette

deck: Mulder manages to obtain a video of a supposed alien  autopsy. But is it genuine, or a fake?
name: Nisei

deck: While continuing to investigate the mysterious autopsy video, Mulder becomes trapped on a train with an NSA agent. His life soon depends on knowing who and what to trust.

description:
Japanese title: Kikyō (帰郷)

A figure passes through the gates. It's an older Naruto, who has returned from a long training journey with Jiraiya. Naruto Uzumaki is back!
name: Homecoming

deck: A killer appears to be targeting supposed bearers of stigmata.
name: Revelations

deck: A small town panics when it appears to be at the mercy of killer cockroaches.
name: War of the Coprophages

description: Darkwing goes on a mission for SHUSH
name: Water Way to Go

deck: A series of deaths involving boys from the same high school leads Mulder and Scully to look closely at a pair of inseparable teenage girls.
name: Syzygy

deck: A murderer claims to be under the influence of a demon.
name: Grotesque

deck: The first "black oil" episode. Mulder and Scully investigate when the crew of a ship suffer inexplicable burns.
name: Piper Maru

deck: As the team continue their search for answers, Director Skinner fights for his life.
name: Apocrypha

deck: Mulder and Scully meet a killer who appears to be able to control others completely, simply by talking to them.
name: Pusher

deck: Strange things begin to happen after the grave of an ancient shaman is disturbed.
name: Teso Dos Bichos

deck: An unexplained death draws attention to an underground gambling ring in which participants' organs are removed from their bodies.
name: Hell Money

deck: Scully agrees to assist an author who is attempting to write a book about an alleged alien abduction.
name: Jose Chung's "From Outer Space"

deck: After spending the night with a woman, Skinner finds himself implicated in her murder.
name: Avatar

deck: Mulder and Scully look into reported sightings of a creature similar to the Loch Ness monster.
name: Quagmire

deck: The Lone Gunmen help Mulder and Scully to get to the bottom of a series of unexplained killings, which seem to involve a TV signal which interferes with people's brains.
name: Wetwired

description:
Japanese title 死神になっちゃった日, Shinigami ni natchatta hi.

Fifteen-year-old Ichigo Kurosaki has the uncanny ability to see ghosts, but that seems pretty run-of-the-mill once Soul Reaper Rukia Kuchiki enters his life.
name: The Day I Became A Shinigami

deck: Following a shooting at a restaurant, a man heals the wounded with his hands, and then disappears.
name: Talitha Cumi

deck: Mulder is taken to a farm operated by strange children, some of whom appear to be clones of his sister.
name: Herrenvolk

deck: The discovery of a dead baby riddled with birth defects raises alarms in a quiet rural town.
name: Home

deck: In the series pilot, the X-Men welcome their newest recruit: Nightcrawler.
description:
Plot Summary:

Note: This episode is the series premiere and introduces multiple characters - primarily, the main cast of the series:

  • Cyclops
  • Jean Grey
  • Magneto (partially obscured)
  • Mystique
  • Nightcrawler
  • Professor X
  • Sabretooth
  • Storm
  • Toad
  • Wolverine
name: Strategy X

deck: When a number of black males are found dead with their bodies somehow stripped of pigment, fear spreads throughout the immigrant community.
name: Teliko

deck: When an unexplained photograph appears to be crucial evidence in a murder investigation, Mulder and Scully entertain the possibility of psychic photography.
name: Unruhe

deck: Teenager Kitty Pryde is horrified when she learns of her ability to walk through walls, prompting a visit by the X-Men.
name: The X-Impulse

deck: During a raid intended to prevent the mass suicide of a religious cult, Mulder meets a woman who is convinced that they were lovers in a previous life.
name: The Field Where I Died

deck: The X-Men attempt to help a girl known as Rogue, who has just recently learned of her ability to drain the life force and memories of people she touches.
name: Rogue Recruit

deck: Fred Dukes, a former sideshow entertainer, arrives at Bayville High. When Jean Grey attempts to help the new student, he begins to mistake her friendship for attraction.
name: Mutant Crush

deck: A group of patients at a cosmetic surgery clinic are horrifically murdered.
name: Sangiunarium

description: Jubilee's foster parents signed her up for the Mutant Registration Program. While at the mall she is attacked by an enormous robot, called a Sentinel. She is saved by other mutants, Storm, Rogue, Gambit, and Cyclops. She is then taken to Xavier's School for Gifted Youngsters, where she is introduced to the team as the X-Men.
name: Night of the Sentinels (Part 1)

deck: Special episode focusing on the life of the Smoking Man, and how he came to work for the Syndicate.
name: Musings of a Cigarette Smoking Man

description: After realizing that the attack on Jubilee is related to the Mutant Registration Program, the X-Men go to the headquarters and destroy the records on mutants. On their way to escape they are stopped by the Sentinels, and Beast is injured and Morph is killed.
name: Night of the Sentinels (Part 2)

deck: The black oil saga continues, as Mulder investigates a supposed camp in Tunguska where people are being deliberately exposed to the oil.
name: Tunguska

description: Norman Osborn hires Spencer Smythe to capture Spider-Man. Smythe releases his deadliest weapon, the Spider Slayer.
name: The Spider Slayer

description: A mass breakout occurs at each of the four supervillain prisons.
name: Breakout, Part 1

description: With the help of Emma Frost, the X-Men discover the location of Professor X. But what will they do when they find out that he's on Magneto's island stronghold... Genosha?
name: Hindsight: Part Three

description: After finding Charles Xavier in a coma, the X-Men are told by his future self, that a great war is coming, and Ororo Munroe aka Storm, starts it. With this new knowledge, Wolverine leads the X-Men to Africa to find her, however, they are not the only ones looking for her.
name: Overflow

deck: Mulder and Krycek struggle to escape after being taken prisoner in Russia.
name: Terma

description:
Beast is in prison, captured after injured by the Sentinels. Magneto attempts to break him out, but Beast declines, preferring to wait for his trial. At the trial, Beast is denied bail, and Sabretooth arrives, and goes into a rage. After being injured, Sabretooth is brought to Xavier's school, which Wolverine is angry about.

Magneto attacks a military missile facility and Wolverine, Cyclops, and Storm arrive to stop him. Storm is able to divert the missiles he launched, and Magneto declares the three of them his enemies.
name: Enter Magneto

deck: A killer who murders little girls and keeps souvenirs from each victim claims to have information on the whereabouts of Mulder's sister.
name: Paper Hearts

description: Professor X attempts to rehabilitate Sabretooth, to the anger of Wolverine. Meanwhile, Magneto attacks a chemical plant to attract Professor X's attention. The X-Men arrive to stop him. While alone with Sabretooth, Jubilee is tricked into releasing him and Sabretooth attacks her. Then, Wolverine shows up to save her.
name: Deadly Reunions

description:
Spencer Smythe's son Alistair is hired by the Kingpin to get revenge on Spider-Man and everyone who had a hand in Spencer's death. He rebuilds the original Spider Slayer, along with two more.

In this episode, Mary Jane utters her famous line "Face it Tiger, you just hit the jackpot".
name: The Return of the Spider-Slayers

deck: A group of immigrants believe a recent death in their community to be the work of El Chupacabra.
name: El Mundo Gira

description: The X-Men train in the "Danger Room" at Xavier's School, and when the room starts closing in around them, Storm's claustrophobia is revealed. While Jean and Scott are out on a date, they see humans chasing down a mutant. They discover that the humans were actually lured into a trap by a group of mutants calling themselves Morlocks. Jean and Scott are kidnapped by the Morlocks, and brought to their underground home. The X-Men go to find them. To get out safely, Storm challenges the leader of the Morlocks to a one-on-one fight. She beats the leader and invites the Morlocks to live at the mansion, but they all decline.
name: Captive Hearts

deck: A man appears to be able to regenerate, becoming effectively invulnerable.
name: Leonard Betts

deck: A man commemorates the end of a bitter divorce by getting a tattoo. But this backfires when the tattoo appears to have a mind of her own.
name: Never Again

deck: Scully discovers that her abduction experience has made her sick, and that she is dying of cancer.
name: Memento Mori

description:
Wolverine leaves the mansion without telling anyone. Jean and Cyclops discover his disappearance, and Cyclops becomes angry at Wolverine's abandonment of the team. In Canada, Wolverine is ambushed by Sabretooth. While fighting, Wolverine falls into an icy lake, but is able to pull himself onto a chunk of ice. He is then saved by a group of fisherman.

Meanwhile, Gambit, Storm, and Jubilee are sent to Genosha, to investigate the apparent welcoming of mutants there. There welcome in Genosha is a trap, however.
name: Cold Vengeance

description: Gambit, Jubilee, and Storm, alongside many other mutants, are forced to do slave labor in Genosha. Storm is thrown into an isolated cell after attempting to escape. Jubilee plans to break out, but her plan is betrayed to the guards by Gambit, and she is thrown into the cell next to Storm's. When Gambit makes a break for it he runs into Cable. Cable helps Gambit get his power inhibitor collar off and then they part ways. Gambit helps Jubilee and Storm escape their cells and they free the other mutants.
name: Slave Island

deck: The victim of a hate crime seems to have come back from the dead.
name: Kaddish

deck: Mulder and Scully attempt to solve a series of murders, but the perpetrator seems to be able to vanish at will.
name: Unrequited

deck: Alien abductee Max Fennig is killed when the plane he is on crashes. But it is evident that there are dangerous forces at work.
name: Tempus Fugit

description:
The X-Men return to the mansion to find it destroyed, and with no sign of Professor X. While searching for whoever destroyed the mansion, Wolverine and Jubilee meet Colossus. Wolverine realizes that Colossus is not the one who destroyed the mansion however. Colossus is arrested for robbing a bank, but claims innocence. Storm and Rogue break Colossus out of prison, while Jubilee and Wolverine track down Juggernaut, breaking into another bank.

In a fight with the X-Men Juggernaut reveals he is not a mutant, and that he is brother to Charles Xavier. The X-Men work to remove Juggernaut's helmet, but when Rogue tries to absorb his powers it is too much for her. Jean uses her power to stop Juggernaut. Colossus fixes the mansion, and declines an offer to join the X-Men, saying he must find his sister.

Note: The Unstoppable Juggernaut was aired out of order originally, airing as episode 10 instead of episode 8.
name: The Unstoppable Juggernaut

deck: As the investigation into Max's death continues, Mulder and Scully wonder whether his abduction history is somehow a factor.
name: Max

deck: Lelouch Lamperouge appears to be a normal, but bored, student. However, his life changes forever when he gains the mysterious power known as Geaas - the power to force anybody to follow any order he gives if he looks into their eyes.
name: The Day a New Demon was Born

series.name: Code Geass: Lelouch of the Rebellion

deck: An old man commits a series of murders, in an attempt to prevent the invention of a compound which could enable humans to travel through time.
name: Synchrony

description: Note: The Cure was originally aired out of order, as episode eight.
name: The Cure

deck: A group of unrelated babies are born with the same genetic anomaly: a tail.
name: Small Potatoes

deck: Storm's nephew, Evan Daniels, discovers his mutant abilities. However, he is hesitant to join his aunt's team.
name: Speed and Spyke

deck: When a woman is killed by a swarm of bees, Skinner finds himself caught in a web of deceit.
name: Zero Sum

deck: Nightcrawler gets pulled into a parallel dimension, where he meets a teenager named Forge - who had been trapped there for 20 years - who wants to return to the real world with Nightcrawler.
name: Middleverse

deck: When a number of young women are murdered, witnesses report seeing the ghosts of the victims right before they die.
name: Elegy

deck: Mystique further tries to keep Rogue away from the X-Men's grasp, arranging for Rogue and Cyclops to be on the same trip, so she can become more distrustful of the X-Men.
name: Turn of the Rogue

deck: Mulder wakes up covered in blood, with no recollection of recent events. But to make sense of his situation, he must dig deep into his past.
name: Demons

deck: Spyke works on an assignment where he decides to film his life living at the Xavier Institute with his friends. However, Sabretooth attempts to get his hands on the camera so he can find Wolverine.
name: SpykeCam

deck: The X Files becomes the target of an investigation, which may lead to the end of the department, and of Mulder and Scully's careers.
name: Gethsemane

deck: The X-Men and the Brotherhood are sent to a survival camp where they have to put aside their differences to work together. Meanwhile, while the X-Men are away from the Institute, Mystique sends Juggernaut after Professor Xavier
description: Note: Introduction of Juggernaut.
name: Survival of the Fittest

deck: As Scully tries her best to delay an investigation, Mulder comes to some startling conclusions.
name: Redux

deck: Rogue suffers from nightmares, which oddly involve Nightcrawler and their mysteriously shared pasts.
description: Note: Kitty's dragon Lockheed makes somewhat of an appearance.
name: Shadowed Past

deck: With Scully rushed into hospital, Mulder is forced to choose between saving her from cancer, and the truth he searched for his entire life.
name: Redux II

deck: Wolverine starts having headaches, which lead to violent outbursts. When Wolverine flies toward what he thinks might be his origin, Shadowcat and Nightcrawler stowaway on the Jet to find out what's happening.
name: Grim Reminder

deck: An origin episode featuring The Lone Gunmen.
name: Unusual Suspects

deck: Scott Summers is reunited with his long-lost brother, Alex Summers. However, their meeting was set up by Magneto, who intends to find out which mutants are worthy of becoming part of his Asteroid M.
name: The Cauldron: Part 1
